# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
vh-solara
.vh-solara

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# OS specific files
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Editor directories and files
.idea
.vscode
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
*.log

refs

# Repo-scoped agent/test artifacts (Playwright traces, reports, screenshots).
tmp/

# Node / web build artifacts. `make web` builds the SPA into a gitignored
# STAGING dir (web/dist-build/), NOT the Go embed source. Embed-producing
# targets (`make build`/`install`/`fixtures`, the release workflow) then
# materialize (copy) the staged bundle into pkg/web/dist/ right before
# `go build`, so the binary embeds the real SPA. Only pkg/web/dist/index.html
# is tracked — a self-contained fallback placeholder that keeps a cold
# `go build`/`go test` working with NO frontend build. `make web` alone never
# touches tracked files; `make build`/materialize overwrites pkg/web/dist/index.html
# locally (restore the committed placeholder before committing).
node_modules/
# Playwright test-results/ output (artifacts + .last-run.json). Can appear at
# the repo root or under web/ depending on the CWD `npx playwright test` runs
# from, so match at any level (no leading slash). web/playwright-report/ is the
# separate HTML report and stays anchored to web/.
test-results/
web/playwright-report/
web/dist-build/
pkg/web/dist/*
!pkg/web/dist/index.html

# Agent-local tooling / config.
.claude/

# vh-solara per-project local data (message attachments, etc.) is ignored, but
# the checked-in managed-project config (.vh-solara/project.jsonc) is NOT — it is
# meant to be committed so the repo can declare its companion processes/views.
.vh-solara/*
!.vh-solara/project.jsonc
# .vh-solara/preferences.jsonc is intentionally ignored local prefs (UI
# agentStyles overlay saved by the editor); covered by .vh-solara/* above.
# vh-agent-harness operator-local state (per-developer model overrides,
# coordinator runs, ssh, cleared-assumptions). NOT committed. The committed
# harness config lives under .vh-agent-harness/ and .opencode/.
.local/

# vh-agent-harness runtime/written state — agent scratch, session/workstream
# state, commit-gate scratch, and Python caches. NOT committed. (The harness's
# own starter .gitignore lists these as "never commit"; .local/ above already
# covers the operator-local .local/* subtrees and tmp/ covers repo scratch.)
.opencode/state/
.opencode/sessions/
.opencode/plans/
.opencode/runs/
.opencode/scripts/__pycache__/
.git/commit-gate/
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
